1
00:00:00,156 --> 00:00:03,500
Tab 1
1
They came up to us between 9.30 and 10

2
00:00:03,769 --> 00:00:05,669
They told us to go downstairs

3
00:00:05,880 --> 00:00:10,900
We asked why, and they told us that the sharia judge had come to pass judgment on us

4
00:00:11,380 --> 00:00:12,742
Interviewer: Did everyone in the room go down, or just you?

5
00:00:12,773 --> 00:00:18,226
Yes, all of us, because we were all sentenced, and it was a Friday, and the judge does not come on Friday

6
00:00:19,856 --> 00:00:24,129
The judge came, and we lined up in a queue that reached the end of the corridor

7
00:00:25,127 --> 00:00:27,687
There were five or six people in front of me

8
00:00:28,553 --> 00:00:35,640
He started calling our names and our charges; he had a register listing the reason for detention

9
00:00:36,763 --> 00:00:39,349
He ordered the detainees to be flogged—some 20, some 50, and some 30 lashes

10
00:00:39,929 --> 00:00:42,280
When my turn came, he asked my name, and I answered, Muhannad Mahmoud Saeed

11
00:00:43,007 --> 00:00:45,474
I stepped forward to him, and he ordered that I be flogged 45 lashes

12
00:00:46,092 --> 00:00:47,098
I turned my back to the flogger

13
00:00:48,945 --> 00:00:53,447
He started flogging me from the top of my shoulders to the soles of my feet

14
00:00:54,381 --> 00:00:55,382
45 lashes

15
00:00:56,719 --> 00:00:58,933
Interviewer: Were your eyes open?
Witness: Yes, they were open

16
00:00:59,127 --> 00:01:03,961
Interviewer: Can you describe the flogger—his manner, build, appearance, and age?

17
00:01:04,166 --> 00:01:08,466
He was, at the time, between 22 and 23 years old

18
00:01:09,089 --> 00:01:12,376
He had dark skin and wasn’t from Mosul

19
00:01:13,055 --> 00:01:16,009
Interviewer: Do you mean from Mosul’s outskirts or from another province?
Witness: No, from the outskirts

20
00:01:18,441 --> 00:01:21,827
He was dark, with a black beard, wearing their Kandahari outfit

21
00:01:21,913 --> 00:01:25,650
He tucked the Quran under his armpit to lessen the harm while flogging

22
00:01:26,020 --> 00:01:29,542
And we had to ask for forgiveness with every lash—they would tell us to ask for forgiveness

23
00:01:30,545 --> 00:01:37,913
After the flogging, the judge told me to collect my belongings

24
00:01:39,428 --> 00:01:43,895
They handed me only the money

25
00:01:43,920 --> 00:01:48,486
They kept the cigarettes to smoke them—they didn’t destroy them

26
00:01:49,574 --> 00:01:52,667
As for IDs, at that time I didn’t have my ID on me

27
00:01:53,014 --> 00:01:56,971
They brought it for me in the afternoon, and it stayed with them

28
00:01:57,328 --> 00:01:58,688
The next day I came back to collect it

29
00:01:58,781 --> 00:02:03,068
I didn’t know that my family had brought it to them when they asked for it

30
00:02:04,025 --> 00:02:07,512
The next day I came back to take my ID

31
00:02:07,731 --> 00:02:14,514
Interviewer: When you stood in the line, how many guards were there besides the flogger?

32
00:02:15,121 --> 00:02:18,887
Alongside the sharia judge there were three or four people

33
00:02:20,800 --> 00:02:22,708
And others were positioned all around us

34
00:02:23,215 --> 00:02:27,376
The judge was considered a big figure, and a security detail accompanied him

35
00:02:28,209 --> 00:02:33,719
Interviewer: While you were standing there as the five in front of you were being flogged

36
00:02:34,236 --> 00:02:37,074
At that time, didn’t you look around at the place or the building?

37
00:02:37,398 --> 00:02:43,269
Did you see the shape of the building or the details in it?

38
00:02:43,407 --> 00:02:48,474
We were standing there—all you can think is that you are about to be flogged

39
00:02:50,552 --> 00:02:55,275
The person in front of me moved while he was being flogged, so they restarted the flogging from the beginning

40
00:02:56,886 --> 00:02:59,238
He was wearing a thin, tight garment

41
00:03:00,561 --> 00:03:07,545
They punished him for trimming his beard after catching him at a checkpoint called Bab al-Sham

42
00:03:08,214 --> 00:03:10,927
He was punished again because of his tight garment

43
00:03:12,603 --> 00:03:17,273
They told the judge that he couldn’t get his hands out to do <i>wudu</i> [ablution]

44
00:03:18,081 --> 00:03:21,834
So the judge ordered them to repeat the flogging, causing him very great pain

45
00:03:22,880 --> 00:03:30,012
Interviewer: Do you think the flogger was flogging you just in obedience to orders?

46
00:03:30,202 --> 00:03:33,497
Or did he harbor hatred toward you?

47
00:03:33,963 --> 00:03:37,678
Both at once

48
00:03:38,535 --> 00:03:42,582
Not only as an application of religious orders, as he claimed

49
00:03:43,021 --> 00:03:44,106
But he also flogs you with a kind of malice

50
00:03:44,984 --> 00:03:47,288
Interviewer: Did you know him before?

51
00:03:47,313 --> 00:03:54,038
No, but because you’re not a supporter or one of them, they hold a grudge against you
